Major News Items in Leading Turkish Newspapers
ANKARA , December 24 ( Xinhua ) -- The following are the major news items in leading Turkish newspapers on Thursday .
Milliyet ( National )
-- Turkish President Suleyman Demirel Wednesday assigned independent deputy and Industry and Trade Minister Yalim Erez to form the 56th government as Democratic Left Party leader Bulent Ecevit failed to get enough support from the parliament .
Demirel did not appoint a political party leader to form the government as no party leader can overcome differences among the political parties in the parliament .
Hurriyet ( Freedom )
-- Turkey and Turkish Cypriot-controlled northern Cyprus Wednesday criticized the U.N. Security Council resolutions 1217 and 1218 adopted on Tuesday regarding the efforts to solve the Cyprus problem .
Turkish Daily News
-- Italian Prime Minister Massimo D ' Alema Wednesday denied reports that his government was involved in negotiations to send Abdullah Ocalan , leader of the outlawed Kurdish Workers ' Party ( PKK ) , to a third country .
D ' Alema said that Ocalan was free to go any where he wants .
